  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Multi-Sector Assistance for Vulnerable, Conflict-Affected Communities in South Sudan Republic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM aims at contributing to prevent, reduce and mitigate protection threats for persons affected by the crisis and the COVID-19 pandemic in South Sudan through the provision of multi-sector life-saving humanitarian assistance. In particular, IOM is supporting affected populations through the provision of water, site care and maintenance, distribution of shelter/non-food items, as well as enhancing the psychological well-being of affected populations through integrated protection programming. In addition, IOM is further strengthening the capacity of the humanitarian aid system by providing timely and targeted humanitarian assistance through information management and cluster coordination.</narrative>
  </description>
